The paper discusses machine learning projects in social computing, specifically those that involve teams of humans labeling data for a particular purpose. This suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper focuses on the methodology of structured content analysis, which is related to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also touches on issues of data quality and reliability, which could fall under the sub-categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Security and Privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD), as it discusses the importance of reliable training data in machine learning projects.
